OL,6,FThe team has decided the most
OL,7,Feffective and efficient way to deal
OL,8,Fwith businesses who repeatedly break
OL,9,Fthe law is to close them down.
OL,11,FAbdul Bari said: "For me a closure
OL,12,Forder has a bigger impact on the
OL,13,Ftrader because effectively a trader is
OL,14,Fbeing forced to close their business
OL,15,Fpremises from three months to half a
OL,16,Fyear and that hits them where it hurts
OL,17,Fthem the most in the pocket - that's
OL,18,Fbetter than a fine."
